Spain Won’t Boost Electricity Rates to Cut Deficit, Europa Says

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-05-11T06:30:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/spain-won-t-boost-electricity-rates-to-cut-deficit-europa-says.html
Spain  doesn’t plan more increases in
electricity rates to reduce the so-called tariff deficit,  Europa
Press  reported yesterday, citing Industry Minister Miguel Sebastian.  The government doesn’t expect any increase in electricity
charges after the extraordinary 10 percent increase this year,
the newswire reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
